narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: YES! This is a class every one interested in Russia and/or Eastern Europe should take.

It's frequently an "awkwardly sized lecture" that functions, in certain respects, more like a seminar. The format turns out to be highly conducive to allowing students to engage with the material without requiring the high level of reading a junior seminar might. As a result, it's a fun course that gets younger History students to pay attention to historiography. That's an unusual concept, and it's one more professors should pay attention to. Take it!
A detailed overview of the Russian empire between its beginnings in Kiev to Catherine the Great's time.
I would receommend it to anyone interested in Russian history, even if it feels obscure at times
